rComments: Has a heart for helping students learn and get their feet wet in the industry of UX design. Invited industry experts to class - you get tangible feedback about the quality of your work frequently. Very long paragraphs of criteria for every assignment, and lots of assignments... be prepared to spend a lot of time meeting the requirements.

In the past, this course was very theoretical but Olivier redesigned it to be more practical insofar that it seems to be more practical-leaning than theoretical-leaning. This is great: in doing qualitative research you actually go beyond doing the weekly readings.  He's extremely accessible and understanding as well.

After finishing this course, you will have a very strong grasp of what IA is and know how to implement IA into your work. This is because theory and practice are equally divided in this course. Olivier explains concepts very clearly. Assignments can occasionally be vague, but he's extremely accessible so that's a basically a very minor problem.
